It's just an autographed CD.

6
00:01:20,290 --> 00:01:23,450
   

7
00:01:28,470 --> 00:01:31,660
   

8
00:01:32,590 --> 00:01:40,160
 It's probably... difficult to suddenly arrange a performance, right? 

9
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:43,040
 I thought it was your sabbatical year. 

10
00:01:43,040 --> 00:01:44,920
 Yeah. 

11
00:01:49,190 --> 00:01:51,630
 But I need money. 

12
00:01:54,530 --> 00:01:56,440
 How much do you need? 

13
00:01:57,590 --> 00:02:00,120
 Around 20 million won. (~$20,000) 

14
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:06,070
 Sorry for asking for such a favor. 

15
00:02:08,810 --> 00:02:15,200
 I'll help you look into it, but it's best you don't hold any expectations. 

16
00:02:15,200 --> 00:02:17,960
 Yeah, I know. 

17
00:02:19,160 --> 00:02:22,270
 The live performance venues are probably all booked by now. 

18
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:25,520
 More than that... 

19
00:02:28,590 --> 00:02:34,880
 Even if you get a venue, it would be hard to sell out the show. 

20
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:39,340
 After Seung Ji Min won the competition, he claimed a lot of the market share. 

21
00:02:39,340 --> 00:02:44,750
 Probably...a lot more than you think. 

22
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:18,180
Please give me lessons.

23
00:03:22,050 --> 00:03:25,090
I'll participate in the Tchaikovsky competition.

24
00:03:32,130 --> 00:03:34,510
 I thought that once the calluses on my fingertips became firmer...  

25
00:03:34,510 --> 00:03:37,290
 He's so handsome! 

26
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:39,540
 So handsome! 

27
00:03:39,540 --> 00:03:43,830
 my heart would grow firmer calluses as well. 

28
00:03:46,070 --> 00:03:48,350
 We... 

29
00:03:50,370 --> 00:03:53,200
 have nothing to do with each other anyway. 

30
00:03:55,910 --> 00:03:58,270
 So, from now on... 

31
00:04:01,730 --> 00:04:04,200
 I'll be fine. 

32
00:04:07,690 --> 00:04:11,200
 I told myself that every day. 

33
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:16,150
 Could you sign mine too? 

34
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:22,860
 Song Ah! 

35
00:04:27,510 --> 00:04:29,390
Song Ah!

36
00:04:31,730 --> 00:04:33,510
Song Ah.

37
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:41,520
Are you okay?

38
00:04:48,910 --> 00:04:51,190
I like you.

39
00:05:00,070 --> 00:05:02,960
I like you, Joon Young.

40
00:05:07,030 --> 00:05:11,760
 That day, I heard his story. 

41
00:05:12,540 --> 00:05:16,590
 About his piano... 

42
00:05:16,590 --> 00:05:18,210
   

43
00:05:18,210 --> 00:05:20,650
  his love, 

44
00:05:22,860 --> 00:05:25,180
 his friend... 

45
00:05:28,150 --> 00:05:31,100
 I heard the sound of his heart, 

46
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:35,550
 his heart that he kept emptying, again and again,  

47
00:05:36,430 --> 00:05:39,490
 because he was afraid that he'd be exposed. 

48
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:45,850
 Playing Träumerei was like a habit of mine. 

49
00:05:47,930 --> 00:05:53,340
Every day, after sitting in front of the piano and playing that song,

50
00:05:56,310 --> 00:06:00,290
my heart that had been so full all night became at least a little bit emptier.

51
00:06:03,690 --> 00:06:07,370
Jung Kyung's mother's accident

52
00:06:07,370 --> 00:06:10,980
didn't happen because of you.

53
00:06:12,010 --> 00:06:14,330
Even so, the feelings in my heart...

54
00:06:15,970 --> 00:06:18,590
aren't that simple.

55
00:06:24,220 --> 00:06:26,670
Sorry for telling you this.

56
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:36,980
I think I need...some time.

57
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,770
Knowing this...

58
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,410
would you wait for me?

59
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:59,430
Yes.

60
00:07:01,290 --> 00:07:03,500
I'll wait for you.

61
00:07:14,260 --> 00:07:22,280
   
   

62
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:03,190
By the way, what sequence number did you get for your graduation performance?

63
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:04,410
I'm the fifth one.

64
00:08:04,410 --> 00:08:07,130
That's good.

65
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:10,380
That... the Franck Sonata.

66
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:12,570
Take it as practice for the stage and play this as your graduation performance,

67
00:08:12,570 --> 00:08:15,840
and take the exam for graduate school.

68
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:17,590
How about your accompanist?

69
00:08:17,590 --> 00:08:23,250
I'm planning to ask the piano major student that I worked with for the practical exam.

70
00:08:24,700 --> 00:08:27,710
You're going to ask a student?

71
00:08:27,710 --> 00:08:30,180
Do you think a school practical exam and a college entrance exam are the same things?

72
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:33,370
The accompanist is extremely important.

73
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:40,980
Violin sonatas are pieces that are composed for the violin and piano.

74
00:08:40,980 --> 00:08:44,030
It's not just a violin piece that requires piano accompaniment.

75
00:08:44,030 --> 00:08:46,960
The two people performing a sonata must breathe in sync,

76
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:50,300
think together, and create music together.

77
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:52,960
You guys are equals. Partners.

78
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:55,480
Yes.

79
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:59,710
If you don't know any pianists, work with her.

80
00:08:59,710 --> 00:09:01,080
She's my friend's daughter.

81
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:04,530
She got a master's in accompaniment at Julliard.

82
00:09:04,530 --> 00:09:07,140
I sent you her contact.

83
00:09:35,590 --> 00:09:39,800
Do you still remember what I said when I first gave you a lesson back then?

84
00:09:42,210 --> 00:09:45,020
"At a competition, you must get seven, eight or nine points

85
00:09:45,020 --> 00:09:48,240
from all the judges no matter what."

86
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:52,310
"A performance that gets ten points from one or two people but six or seven from the rest

87
00:09:52,310 --> 00:09:57,470
can never win in a competition." This is what I said.

88
00:09:57,470 --> 00:10:02,410
Yes. I've never forgotten.

89
00:10:02,410 --> 00:10:04,920
You're really good at that.

90
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:08,050
You know how to adequately satisfy others.

91
00:10:08,050 --> 00:10:13,030
No matter what field you're in, it's an ability to be able to know what you're good at.

92
00:10:13,030 --> 00:10:16,460
So it's the same this time.

93
00:10:16,460 --> 00:10:20,040
Do what you're good at, not what you want to do. Got it?

94
00:10:21,020 --> 00:10:22,590
Yes.

95
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:30,200
Music exists only when the people who will listen to it exists.

96
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:33,770
If you don't want to be pressing keys in an empty room by yourself,

97
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:36,700
win the competition.

98
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:39,760
Though without my words,

99
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:43,310
you're probably much more desperate.

100
00:10:48,230 --> 00:10:50,570
   

101
00:10:51,310 --> 00:10:54,070
Section Chief. Section Chief, Section Chief!

102
00:10:54,070 --> 00:10:56,050
Mmh?

103
00:10:56,690 --> 00:10:59,540
Master Joon Young made a contract with Chris's company

104
00:10:59,540 --> 00:11:02,310
after getting that prize at the Chopin competition, right?

105
00:11:02,310 --> 00:11:06,690
And Chris gave the Korean management rights to Kyunghoo.

106
00:11:06,690 --> 00:11:11,690
Yes. It was a sort of outsourcing, in remembrance of their past relationship.

107
00:11:11,690 --> 00:11:15,610
But... what if Chris really

108
00:11:15,610 --> 00:11:19,750
takes back the Korean management rights over Master Joon Young?

109
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:23,190
Won't he be putting Master Joon Young under another company, then?

110
00:11:23,190 --> 00:11:27,330
Master Joon Young and Chris still have a few years left to their contract, after all.

111
00:11:28,170 --> 00:11:31,200
Team Leader will probably take care of it.

112
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:33,050
Pardon?

113
00:11:33,050 --> 00:11:36,040
Ah, yes.

114
00:11:37,370 --> 00:11:39,320
 It all sounds like an excuse to us. Unfortunately,  

115
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:44,890
 you leave us no choice but to take back Kyunghoo's management rights of Joon Young in Korea. 

116
00:11:44,890 --> 00:11:47,770
Wait— Hello? Chris!

117
00:11:54,660 --> 00:11:58,580
Unni, did you decide on the piece you'll play at the graduation performance?

118
00:11:58,580 --> 00:12:00,900
Franck's sonata.

119
00:12:00,900 --> 00:12:04,470
That's the piece for the graduate school entrance exam, no? Did the professor tell you to play that?

120
00:12:04,470 --> 00:12:06,150
Yes.

121
00:12:07,090 --> 00:12:11,160
Oh, there... It's Park Joon Young!

122
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:16,680
He's looking at us.

123
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:26,170
Excuse me... Is it alright if I sit here?

124
00:12:37,370 --> 00:12:42,560
You're also taking fourth-year classes, but none of ours overlap with the piano majors'.

125
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:44,440
It's such a pity.

126
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:47,330
Then you'll be holding a graduation performance too! I'll go see you.

127
00:12:47,330 --> 00:12:49,270
Me too!

128
00:12:49,270 --> 00:12:51,770
Yes, please come.

129
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:55,860
- We have class. 
 - Already?

130
00:12:55,860 --> 00:12:57,580
We'll be on our way.

131
00:12:57,580 --> 00:12:59,010
We'll see you later.

132
00:12:59,010 --> 00:13:00,540
Unni, enjoy your lunch!

133
00:13:00,540 --> 00:13:02,120
Sure.

134
00:13:13,550 --> 00:13:17,550
Why aren't you saying anything? As if we're strangers.

135
00:13:19,650 --> 00:13:21,750
Who are you?

136
00:13:24,880 --> 00:13:30,520
♫   Though I'm alone, I long for your warm smile   ♫

137
00:13:36,820 --> 00:13:45,140
♫   Even the sunlight reminds me of your bright eyes    ♫

138
00:13:46,150 --> 00:13:49,160
Is it your first time at the student's union?

139
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:52,160
Well, it's my first time in this place, except for the cafeteria downstairs.

140
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:53,860
There are so many clubs.

141
00:13:53,860 --> 00:13:55,050
   

142
00:13:55,050 --> 00:13:58,810
So you plan on joining one if there's any you like? 
    

143
00:13:58,810 --> 00:14:03,260
Can I join even if I can only be active for two months before graduating?

144
00:14:03,260 --> 00:14:05,520
No, of course not.

145
00:14:07,420 --> 00:14:10,030
- Ah, it's over there. 
 - Ah.

146
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,880
So that is SRUPO.

147
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:15,350
The place where you spent your youth.

148
00:14:15,350 --> 00:14:18,720
Pardon? My youth?

149
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:20,660
   

150
00:14:21,340 --> 00:14:24,300
Yes, well, that's right.

151
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:28,360
Since this is also where I made the decision to go to Music School.

152
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:33,640
But actually I haven't been here in a very long time,

153
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:37,240
so I don't really know the current members...

154
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:41,210
Ah but they will recognize you!

155
00:14:41,210 --> 00:14:42,860
They'll be so surprised.

156
00:14:42,860 --> 00:14:46,500
♫   Everything looks like you,    ♫

157
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:47,720
♫  my love  ♫

158
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:51,430
♫   I remember everything single part of you   ♫

159
00:14:51,430 --> 00:14:54,350
No one is here...

160
00:14:56,350 --> 00:15:00,370
- W-well so, it's locked, right? 
 - Yes. 
 - Right?

161
00:15:02,820 --> 00:15:05,290
Where are you going now? To Kyunghoo?

162
00:15:05,290 --> 00:15:08,470
No, I plan on practicing at the school today.

163
00:15:08,470 --> 00:15:12,210
Because I can't use the rehearsal room at Kyunghoo when there is a concert.

164
00:15:12,210 --> 00:15:13,960
What about you?

165
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:17,750
Me, well, I'll just go home.

166
00:15:20,170 --> 00:15:22,830
Uhm, tomorrow...

167
00:15:23,940 --> 00:15:26,670
I mean, tomorrow, uhm...

168
00:15:26,670 --> 00:15:29,670
At what times do you have classes?

169
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:35,590
I only have one class in the afternoon tomorrow.

170
00:15:36,790 --> 00:15:40,960
Do you want to go for ice cream at the student union tomorrow?

171
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:42,880
They still sell some, right?

172
00:15:46,490 --> 00:15:49,770
Yes. I'd be happy to.

173
00:16:27,230 --> 00:16:30,180
It taste's the same as in the old days. Though the price is 500 won  (≈ $0.50)  higher now.

174
00:16:30,180 --> 00:16:31,820
Mm?

175
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:34,880
What is it?

176
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:41,040
It's just that... you really talk like an old person.

177
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:43,730
What are you saying? We're the same age.

178
00:16:44,860 --> 00:16:47,220
Oh... 
 ♫   I like everything about you   ♫

179
00:16:47,220 --> 00:16:49,710
♫   Are you listening to my confession for you?   ♫

180
00:16:49,710 --> 00:16:52,730
Your shoelace is undone. Hold this for a second.

181
00:16:54,130 --> 00:16:56,010
I don't want to.

182
00:16:56,950 --> 00:16:59,260
I'll tie it myself.

183
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:05,000
♫   Though I'm alone, I long for your warm smile   ♫

184
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:10,520
You know how in movies, the guy always ties the girl's shoelaces?

185
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:12,520
Movies?

186
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:13,930
Yes.

187
00:17:13,930 --> 00:17:17,090
Then the girl falls for the guy.

188
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:20,870
But I don't want to fall for you.

189
00:17:22,810 --> 00:17:24,690
Give it to me.

190
00:17:25,530 --> 00:17:28,290
♫   To the place you are, I   ♫

191
00:17:28,290 --> 00:17:32,540
♫   I want to go right now   ♫

192
00:17:32,540 --> 00:17:34,870
Please don't laugh, I'm being serious.

193
00:17:34,870 --> 00:17:37,050
Okay.

194
00:17:39,010 --> 00:17:41,510
♫   Will you always stay by my side?   ♫

195
00:17:41,510 --> 00:17:44,300
I said, don't laugh.

196
00:17:45,490 --> 00:17:48,060
♫   I remember everything single part of you   ♫

197
00:17:48,060 --> 00:17:49,960
Alright.

198
00:17:50,650 --> 00:17:58,610
♫   Again, I long for you   ♫

199
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:07,860
Here.

200
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:26,250
I'll just go wash my hands in the bathroom.

201
00:18:30,540 --> 00:18:33,600
 Let me remind you that although this teaching staff recruitment session 

202
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:36,510
is to fill the vacancy created by the retirement

203
00:18:36,510 --> 00:18:38,650
of violin professor Song Jung Hee,

204
00:18:38,650 --> 00:18:41,700
the position in itself is for a string music major.

205
00:18:41,700 --> 00:18:45,600
Thus, we will pick only one person with the highest score

206
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:48,680
among all violin, viola, cello and contrabass players here.

207
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:52,320
We ask the applicants to check the date of your master class, recital and interview

208
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:54,790
on the homepage of the  faculty of music.

209
00:18:54,790 --> 00:18:57,120
Thank you for your attention.

210
00:19:15,100 --> 00:19:17,630
Excuse me for a minute, then.

211
00:19:17,630 --> 00:19:19,470
Give it to me.

212
00:19:19,470 --> 00:19:21,060
Sorry?

213
00:19:21,060 --> 00:19:23,640
Leave your violin with me.

214
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:35,130
You can't go anywhere with it.

215
00:19:35,130 --> 00:19:38,310
Of course. I won't run away.

216
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:41,930
You can trust me.

217
00:19:51,530 --> 00:19:54,230
I didn't know you applied as well.

218
00:19:54,230 --> 00:19:56,850
You should have told me.

219
00:19:56,850 --> 00:19:58,780
Aren't you angry?

220
00:19:59,540 --> 00:20:01,230
About what?

221
00:20:03,270 --> 00:20:06,370
I'm going to compete with you.

222
00:20:07,470 --> 00:20:10,550
I'm trying to steal your position. Aren't you angry about that?

223
00:20:11,180 --> 00:20:14,070
What right do I have to be angry at you?

224
00:20:14,070 --> 00:20:17,760
When you and I are nothing to each other.

225
00:20:20,330 --> 00:20:24,250
It looks like you're going on your own path, so I feel at ease.

226
00:20:26,890 --> 00:20:28,860
You feel at ease?

227
00:20:29,690 --> 00:20:31,820
You feel relieved?

228
00:20:33,570 --> 00:20:36,570
Then how do you want me to be?

229
00:20:36,570 --> 00:20:38,940
We broke up.

230
00:20:38,940 --> 00:20:40,000
Then what do you want me to do?

231
00:20:44,830 --> 00:20:47,020
Jung Kyung.

232
00:20:47,580 --> 00:20:50,020
What did I do wrong?

233
00:20:50,550 --> 00:20:54,070
Did I ever do anything that wasn't to your liking?

234
00:20:54,070 --> 00:20:56,590
What did I do so wrong, that you'd do this?

235
00:20:59,740 --> 00:21:02,730
I kept thinking about what I could have done wrong.

236
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:05,560
What did I miss, for you to leave me?

237
00:21:05,570 --> 00:21:08,030
But no matter how hard I think about it,

238
00:21:08,030 --> 00:21:11,040
I've done nothing other than look only at you for ten years.

239
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:15,820
Is that wrong? Did you get tired of it? Is that any way to act in consideration of our ten years together?

240
00:21:15,820 --> 00:21:19,820
What do you want me to? Did I hide anything from you?

241
00:21:19,820 --> 00:21:25,330
I told you that my feelings were wavering. I asked you to hold onto me.

242
00:21:26,830 --> 00:21:29,460
But you didn't do anything.

243
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:33,760
It's not that I didn't want to, it's that I couldn't.

244
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:39,090
Because what was making you waver... was Park Joon Young.

245
00:21:42,160 --> 00:21:43,800
You're right.

246
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:48,450
I love Joon Young, Hyeon Ho.

247
00:21:49,780 --> 00:21:54,250
I... I love him.

248
00:21:54,250 --> 00:21:55,900
Stop it.

249
00:21:55,900 --> 00:21:59,000
Hyeon Ho, she's just saying whatever out of anger—

250
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:03,390
Did you like Jung Kyung?

251
00:22:08,230 --> 00:22:10,780
Woah. How could you...

252
00:22:18,090 --> 00:22:19,890
 Is this the one I gave you?  

253
00:22:19,890 --> 00:22:22,630
  When you did your Chopin Piano Competition? 

254
00:22:23,330 --> 00:22:24,820
 Yeah. 

255
00:22:26,880 --> 00:22:28,610
 Here. 

256
00:22:45,580 --> 00:22:49,260
How could you, to me- How could you like Jung- Hey!

257
00:22:49,260 --> 00:22:52,710
How could this happen, when you've been watching us for ten years?

258
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:54,090
Huh?

259
00:22:54,690 --> 00:22:58,070
Park Joon Young. Tell me.

260
00:22:58,070 --> 00:22:59,780
- Tell me, you— 
 - Han Hyeon Ho.

261
00:22:59,780 --> 00:23:02,170
If you have something to say, say it to me.

262
00:23:26,430 --> 00:23:29,270
 You two... 

263
00:23:29,270 --> 00:23:31,790
What did you do in New York?

264
00:23:35,840 --> 00:23:39,090
