294
00:27:26,610 --> 00:27:30,140
♫   Make me sad   ♫

295
00:27:30,140 --> 00:27:35,160
♫   You're leaving like this, but   ♫

296
00:27:35,160 --> 00:27:39,200
♫   If you can be happy   ♫

297
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:43,840
♫   That's enough for me   ♫

298
00:27:44,690 --> 00:27:49,860
♫   While watching your shrinking figure  ♫

299
00:27:49,860 --> 00:27:52,690
♫   I can't bring myself   ♫

300
00:27:52,690 --> 00:27:58,890
♫  to ask you to wait for me   ♫

301
00:28:04,770 --> 00:28:07,000
Give it to me.

302
00:28:08,460 --> 00:28:12,330
Give that to me. I'll hold it for you.

303
00:28:13,610 --> 00:28:15,310
Ah...

304
00:28:16,710 --> 00:28:21,090
I won't run away with it.

305
00:28:21,990 --> 00:28:24,200
 Give it to me. 

306
00:28:30,010 --> 00:28:32,840
 You can't go anywhere with it. 

307
00:28:33,630 --> 00:28:36,660
 Of course. I won't run away. 

308
00:28:38,210 --> 00:28:40,150
 You can trust me. 

309
00:28:41,860 --> 00:28:45,390
♫   These tears that have gotten cold   ♫

310
00:28:45,390 --> 00:28:48,760
No thank you, I'm alright. 
