00:30:54,070 --> 00:30:56,750
It doesn't, right?

337
00:30:58,460 --> 00:31:00,410
Chae Song Ah!

338
00:31:00,410 --> 00:31:02,030
Huh?

339
00:31:02,940 --> 00:31:05,580
You weren't listening, were you?

340
00:31:06,290 --> 00:31:09,100
- Oh, sorry, how far did we get?
 - Hmph!

341
00:31:14,840 --> 00:31:20,790
Eun Ji told me that Yoon Dong Yoon really is going on blind dates.

342
00:31:29,640 --> 00:31:35,290
But what's wrong with your face? Did something bad happen?

343
00:31:35,290 --> 00:31:37,860
Oh, no. It's nothing.

344
00:31:38,830 --> 00:31:43,900
No...there's definitely something going on.

345
00:31:43,900 --> 00:31:46,430
I told you it's nothing.

346
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:52,660
Miss Chae Song Ah! Who are you trying to fool?

347
00:31:52,660 --> 00:31:55,230
It's written all over your face!

348
00:31:55,230 --> 00:31:57,990
N-no it isn't!

349
00:31:59,330 --> 00:32:02,560
What is it? Tell me.

350
00:32:08,820 --> 00:32:11,370
Well,  you see...

351
00:32:13,970 --> 00:32:17,030
I have someone I like now.

352
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:21,860
Someone you like? Who?

353
00:32:21,860 --> 00:32:24,210
Is it someone I know?

354
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:30,020
Park Joon Young. It's Joon Young.

355
00:32:30,020 --> 00:32:33,020
The p-pianist Park Joon Young?!

356
00:32:37,380 --> 00:32:40,820
Does he know that you like him?

357
00:32:40,820 --> 00:32:44,360
- He should. Because I confessed to him. 
- Huh?!

358
00:32:44,360 --> 00:32:47,230
Confessed?! You?!

359
00:32:47,230 --> 00:32:49,410
- Hey, not so loud.
- Ah...

360
00:32:51,790 --> 00:32:57,900
- So, Chae Song Ah confessed. To a guy.
- Yeah.

361
00:32:57,900 --> 00:33:01,980
I confessed to him.

362
00:33:01,980 --> 00:33:06,900
So? What did he say after you confessed?

363
00:33:08,320 --> 00:33:11,300
He asked me to wait.

364
00:33:11,300 --> 00:33:16,480
But...I don't think he'll come to me.

365
00:33:18,220 --> 00:33:21,750
He would've come to me already if so.

366
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:29,930
Why is the weather so nice?

367
00:33:31,890 --> 00:33:33,750
I know right?

368
00:34:36,240 --> 00:34:38,480
Yes, Noona it's me.

369
00:34:39,450 --> 00:34:42,450
How is Chairman Na?

370
00:34:46,310 --> 00:34:47,680
Oh, that's a relief.

371
00:34:47,680 --> 00:34:50,790
 I just arrived at the hospital. Do you want to come with me? 

372
00:34:50,790 --> 00:34:52,750
I think she'd be happy to see you.

373
00:34:52,750 --> 00:34:55,120
 Oh, no. I'll visit next... 

374
00:34:55,120 --> 00:34:57,250
Next time I'll go.

375
00:34:58,900 --> 00:35:00,640
Yes.

376
00:35:10,730 --> 00:35:15,610
Joon Young is losing his Korean management rights?

377
00:35:15,610 --> 00:35:22,870
Yes. I'm trying to change Chris's mind, but it's hard through the phone.

378
00:35:25,080 --> 00:35:29,550
Forgive me. It's all because of my carelessness.

379
00:35:29,550 --> 00:35:31,910
What does Joon Young think?

380
00:35:32,720 --> 00:35:35,190
I haven't told him yet.

381
00:35:35,190 --> 00:35:39,770
I did talk with him about something else, but seeing how he didn't mention it,

382
00:35:39,770 --> 00:35:42,600
it looks like he's unaware.

383
00:35:45,120 --> 00:35:49,320
Joon Young must have resumed lessons with Professor Yoo?

384
00:35:49,320 --> 00:35:51,570
Yes.

385
00:35:51,570 --> 00:35:57,550
Team Leader Cha. Isn't it uncomfortable with Professor Yoo there?

386
00:35:57,550 --> 00:35:59,680
It's been a long time since we separated.

387
00:35:59,680 --> 00:36:03,560
I'm not exactly comfortable, but there's nothing uncomfortable about it either.

388
00:36:08,770 --> 00:36:13,370
Love, too, is nothing special once it passes.

389
00:36:15,050 --> 00:36:19,870
Life has too many obligations for you to live just chasing after love.

390
00:36:19,870 --> 00:36:22,230
How could you realize that when you're young?

391
00:36:22,230 --> 00:36:26,600
I was the same, so...

392
00:36:29,990 --> 00:36:32,440
I intentionally hurt him.

393
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:37,660
 Joon Young, this is why you won't succeed. 

394
00:36:37,660 --> 00:36:40,740
 If some do exceptionally well while others lag behind, 

395
00:36:40,740 --> 00:36:45,010
 then you get spiteful thoughts. 

396
00:36:46,290 --> 00:36:50,680
With the passing of time, would he understand?

397
00:36:50,680 --> 00:36:54,340
Right now, love is everything, so he'd likely feel bitter.

398
00:36:54,340 --> 00:36:57,420
Why I shook him about like that.

399
00:36:59,170 --> 00:37:01,360
Later...

400
00:37:02,160 --> 00:37:07,900
No... even if he never understands me, it's fine.

401
00:37:07,900 --> 00:37:12,860
But... I don't feel too great about it.

402
00:37:15,820 --> 00:37:21,790
I do selfishly want to remain a good person in everyone's thoughts.

403
00:37:24,390 --> 00:37:26,560
You're already a good person,

404
00:37:26,560 --> 00:37:29,260
To so many people.

405
00:37:41,710 --> 00:37:44,190
This is so annoying!

406
00:37:44,190 --> 00:37:47,490
Mom, they told me to wait.

407
00:37:47,490 --> 00:37:51,890
Attorney Kim said if I waited, he'd get the case for me.

408
00:37:51,890 --> 00:37:53,850
But it's going straight to Attorney Jang!

409
00:37:53,850 --> 00:37:56,090
I thought it was going to Jang anyway?

410
00:37:56,090 --> 00:37:58,560
Still he promised to give it to me!

411
00:37:58,560 --> 00:38:02,560
 Oh let go of it already. Is that the only case available in your law firm? Do something else. 

412
00:38:02,560 --> 00:38:06,600
I don't want to! I trusted he'd give it to me so I made all the preparations!

413
00:38:06,600 --> 00:38:08,470
Ah! This is so annoying!

414
00:38:08,470 --> 00:38:12,520
You should know how to be patient!

415
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:14,580
How can two sisters be this different?

416
00:38:14,580 --> 00:38:19,920
What about me? Would you rather I live like a frustrating moron like that?

417
00:38:19,920 --> 00:38:22,200
What did I do?

418
00:38:22,200 --> 00:38:25,440
 This won't do. I'm going to protest this to Attorney Kim. 

419
00:38:25,440 --> 00:38:29,120
What are you going to protest? You probably didn't get it because you weren't as good as Attorney Jang.

420
00:38:29,120 --> 00:38:33,600
It's not true! Ah, that was supposed to be mine!

421
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:36,520
He shouldn't have told me to wait for it!

422
00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:43,410
I stayed up so many nights for it. How could Attorney Kim do this to me?

423
00:38:53,420 --> 00:38:55,230
 What's up with her? 

424
00:39:05,280 --> 00:39:07,420
Mom.

425
00:39:11,580 --> 00:39:16,400
Oh...I was watching a movie with Seung Hoo.

426
00:39:17,820 --> 00:39:22,260
Did I say I wasn't going to practice today? I'll do it when I get home!

427
00:39:23,630 --> 00:39:27,810
Stop talking about Julliard! You couldn't make it either!

428
00:39:33,090 --> 00:39:34,130
You should've been more careful!

429
00:39:34,130 --> 00:39:35,630
I'm so sorry!

430
00:39:35,630 --> 00:39:36,910
- Let me... 
- No, I got it.

431
00:39:36,910 --> 00:39:38,120
Get me some tissues instead.

432
00:39:38,120 --> 00:39:40,640
- No, I got it. 
- I said it's fine...

433
00:39:43,080 --> 00:39:45,080
Seung Hoo...

434
00:39:46,260 --> 00:39:47,290
You see that's...

435
00:39:47,290 --> 00:39:51,360
Is this...an application?

436
00:39:51,360 --> 00:39:53,200
Didn't you apply to Julliard?

437
00:39:53,200 --> 00:39:56,530
   

438
00:40:11,820 --> 00:40:13,570
Yes?

439
00:40:14,970 --> 00:40:16,640
- Song Ah. 
- Oh, Dad.

440
00:40:16,640 --> 00:40:19,970
- You want to have a can with me?
- Yeah.

441
00:40:31,380 --> 00:40:33,110
- Song Ah
- Yeah?

442
00:40:33,110 --> 00:40:33,960
Just then...

443
00:40:34,740 --> 00:40:37,300
What your sister said earlier... Don't take it to heart.

444
00:40:37,300 --> 00:40:40,420
I scolded her.

445
00:40:48,820 --> 00:40:51,840
- Dad. 
 - Yeah?

446
00:40:53,830 --> 00:41:01,260
Do others think that people who wait quietly are frustrating?

447
00:41:05,910 --> 00:41:08,560
I'm also good at waiting.

448
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:12,120
I wait for the bus, for the subway,

449
00:41:12,120 --> 00:41:15,610
and for my meal at the restaurant.

450
00:41:20,460 --> 00:41:24,750
Song Ah. I...

451
00:41:26,620 --> 00:41:31,260
I am waiting to see how you'll find your happiness.

452
00:41:31,260 --> 00:41:38,830
No matter the path you take, I believe you will find

453
00:41:38,830 --> 00:41:41,230
the path that makes you happiest.

454
00:41:47,270 --> 00:41:49,360
Thank you.

455
00:41:57,520 --> 00:42:00,210
You've gotten more CDs.

456
00:42:06,620 --> 00:42:10,080
"Violinist Chae Song Ah."

457
00:42:11,060 --> 00:42:11,970
It looks cool.

