459
00:42:16,310 --> 00:42:21,430
So he signed like that because you were carrying a violin at the concert hall.

460
00:42:23,840 --> 00:42:26,150
He's a nice person.

461
00:42:28,760 --> 00:42:30,390
Yeah.

462
00:42:31,770 --> 00:42:34,220
He's a nice person.

463
00:43:35,270 --> 00:43:36,790
 Is this the one I gave you?  

464
00:43:36,790 --> 00:43:39,560
  When you did your Chopin Piano Competition? 

465
00:43:49,340 --> 00:43:51,240
 Here. 

466
00:44:05,680 --> 00:44:08,500
I even made the time to come here.

467
00:44:16,640 --> 00:44:18,710
You're here.

468
00:44:20,350 --> 00:44:23,130
Were you practicing with your accompanist?

469
00:44:23,130 --> 00:44:23,980
Yes.

470
00:44:23,980 --> 00:44:29,020
But I don't like her, so I'll look for someone else.

471
00:44:29,020 --> 00:44:30,730
I see.

472
00:44:32,710 --> 00:44:34,720
Get some rest, then.

473
00:44:35,630 --> 00:44:37,890
Yes. You too.

474
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:47,150
Dad. I broke up.

475
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:51,180
With Hyeon Ho?

476
00:44:51,180 --> 00:44:55,340
Yes. You remember his name.

477
00:44:57,520 --> 00:45:03,200
Jung Kyung. I realized that as time passes,

478
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:09,030
the scars I caused remained longer in my mind than the scars I received.

479
00:45:12,450 --> 00:45:14,810
So you too...

480
00:45:16,390 --> 00:45:19,460
 don't hurt anyone too deeply. 

481
00:45:39,500 --> 00:45:42,360
You worked hard, Teacher.

482
00:45:42,360 --> 00:45:43,610
No, it's alright.

483
00:45:43,610 --> 00:45:47,860
If she works hard, she can also go to Seoryeong University like you, right?

484
00:45:47,860 --> 00:45:51,670
I'm not even asking for her to get first place for the practical exam like you did.

485
00:45:51,670 --> 00:45:53,250
She is working hard these days.

486
00:45:53,250 --> 00:45:54,450
I told you.

487
00:45:54,450 --> 00:45:58,480
Just make it into Seoryeong University, and you'll see, I'll do everything you want.

488
00:45:58,480 --> 00:46:01,980
Teach! You heard that, right? You're my witness.

489
00:46:01,980 --> 00:46:03,540
Oh, sure.

490
00:46:06,690 --> 00:46:08,770
I'm so forgetful. Here's the payment for today's lesson.

491
00:46:08,770 --> 00:46:10,260
Here you go.

492
00:46:10,260 --> 00:46:11,890
Thank you.

493
00:46:11,890 --> 00:46:14,940
Your parents must have been so happy.

494
00:46:14,940 --> 00:46:16,600
No, not at all.

495
00:46:36,510 --> 00:46:38,650
Welcome!

496
00:46:41,840 --> 00:46:43,430
You scared me.

497
00:46:43,430 --> 00:46:45,460
What's wrong with you, Han Hyeon Ho?

498
00:46:45,460 --> 00:46:47,320
My back hurts!

499
00:46:47,320 --> 00:46:49,980
- Mom. 
 - Yes.

500
00:46:49,980 --> 00:46:53,090
I'll be a good son soon. Just wait a little bit.

501
00:46:53,090 --> 00:46:57,930
A good son? Why are you asking me to wait, instead of doing it now?

502
00:46:57,930 --> 00:47:02,080
You...! And you won't be good to me?

503
00:47:02,080 --> 00:47:05,330
Of course, you two come as a set, with Mom.

504
00:47:05,330 --> 00:47:07,180
We're a set, we are.

505
00:47:07,180 --> 00:47:11,280
Ah right. Tell Joon Young to come for a meal sometime. Tell him I'll make something delicious.

506
00:47:11,280 --> 00:47:15,440
Why do you never tell him to bring Jung Kyung, even if just to be polite?

507
00:47:15,440 --> 00:47:17,390
Are you being jealous of your son's lover?

508
00:47:17,390 --> 00:47:19,350
You really don't know anything.

509
00:47:19,350 --> 00:47:24,190
They aren't even married, so if I tell her to come she'll be uncomfortable.

510
00:47:24,190 --> 00:47:27,340
And Jung Kyung probably doesn't eat such a thing like our home-cooked meals.

511
00:47:27,340 --> 00:47:29,430
Right?

512
00:47:29,430 --> 00:47:31,460
Ah, I'm so tired.

513
00:47:31,460 --> 00:47:33,510
I gave three lessons today, I'm so tired.

514
00:47:33,510 --> 00:47:34,580
- You're tired? Alright, go. 
 - Okay.

515
00:47:34,580 --> 00:47:36,190
- Go get some rest. 
 - I'm off.

516
00:47:36,190 --> 00:47:39,140
- I'm going. 
 - Yes, see you later.

517
00:47:51,500 --> 00:47:53,980
It's hot, let's go inside to talk.

518
00:48:02,780 --> 00:48:04,630
Actually no.

519
00:48:06,760 --> 00:48:09,190
Let's just talk here.

520
00:48:13,300 --> 00:48:15,260
Why did you come?

521
00:48:23,450 --> 00:48:25,390
I'm sorry.

522
00:48:26,730 --> 00:48:28,590
About what?

523
00:48:31,730 --> 00:48:33,940
It was a lie.

524
00:48:33,940 --> 00:48:36,620
When I said Joon Yeong and I slept together.

525
00:48:40,180 --> 00:48:42,890
Is that so important now?

526
00:48:45,150 --> 00:48:47,290
You saying that you—

527
00:48:51,960 --> 00:48:55,160
The fact that you said that...

528
00:48:56,750 --> 00:48:59,400
Made me understand your feelings well enough.

529
00:49:12,840 --> 00:49:15,660
Do you know why I applied to Seoryeong University?

530
00:49:19,810 --> 00:49:22,340
I have to do something, anything.

531
00:49:23,160 --> 00:49:29,200
Graduating from Seoryeong with top honors or having a doctorate from Indiana is no use, actually.

532
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:35,570
There are too many cellists as good as me in South Korea, and I don't have much money.

533
00:49:36,260 --> 00:49:39,590
I needed to do something to put food on the table.

534
00:49:39,590 --> 00:49:42,550
- Hyeon Ho— 
 - The second reason is...

535
00:50:06,160 --> 00:50:09,230
I wanted to stand on a place similar to yours.

536
00:50:14,890 --> 00:50:17,820
I didn't want to make you feel ashamed. Yeah.

537
00:50:19,220 --> 00:50:22,640
I wanted to be someone who was somewhat suitable

538
00:50:24,900 --> 00:50:27,450
to be next to you.

539
00:50:33,250 --> 00:50:33,960
That was my effort

540
00:50:34,030 --> 00:50:36,570
and my love, I think.

541
00:50:39,760 --> 00:50:42,400
It's all futile now, isn't it?

542
00:51:02,840 --> 00:51:04,870
Goodbye.

543
00:51:06,760 --> 00:51:09,440
And don't come find me again.

544
00:51:10,600 --> 00:51:17,710
♫   I guess you can't express everything with love    ♫

545
00:51:17,710 --> 00:51:24,710
♫   Those words of yours make me sad   ♫

546
00:51:24,710 --> 00:51:29,870
♫   You're leaving like this   ♫

547
00:51:29,870 --> 00:51:38,000
♫   but if you can be happy, that's enough for me  ♫

548
00:51:39,250 --> 00:51:47,300
♫   These tears that have gotten cold 
 cannot be considered part of our farewell  ♫

549
00:51:47,300 --> 00:51:53,290
♫   Come back to me a bit less late   ♫

550
00:51:53,290 --> 00:52:01,930
♫   Even these tears that are falling 
 will become   ♫

551
00:52:01,930 --> 00:52:10,400
♫   Part of my last farewell to you, take care   ♫

552
00:52:38,620 --> 00:52:40,970
Alright, Song Ah.

553
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:43,600
Yes?

554
00:52:43,600 --> 00:52:46,070
Let's stop here for today.

555
00:52:48,030 --> 00:52:49,680
Yes.

556
00:52:56,610 --> 00:53:00,100
- Professor, this—
 - Yes, ahjumma?

557
00:53:00,940 --> 00:53:02,390
Sorry?

558
00:53:03,440 --> 00:53:06,500
No, not the living room. The curtains in the master bedroom.

559
00:53:06,500 --> 00:53:10,020
Take them off and bring them to the dry cleaner.

560
00:53:10,020 --> 00:53:13,600
Oh, and in the morning my eldest...

561
00:53:15,300 --> 00:53:20,370
Joon Young. Are you seeing a violinist these days?

562
00:53:22,210 --> 00:53:23,970
Pardon?

563
00:53:25,740 --> 00:53:29,790
I heard that girl is being really pushy to try to get involved with you.

564
00:53:29,790 --> 00:53:31,560
Is that true?

565
00:53:32,510 --> 00:53:34,940
She's not that kind of person.

566
00:53:36,580 --> 00:53:38,900
Why so serious?

567
00:53:41,650 --> 00:53:44,660
But is there really someone?

568
00:53:45,460 --> 00:53:48,070
This world is smaller than you think.

569
00:53:48,070 --> 00:53:52,010
Whether you date or break up, people are too happy to tittle-tattle about it.

570
00:53:52,010 --> 00:53:55,050
That reputation lasts a really long time afterward.

571
00:53:55,050 --> 00:54:00,660
So if you are seeing someone, prevent rumors from spreading for that person's well-being.

572
00:54:09,100 --> 00:54:10,500
Song Ah, here.

573
00:54:11,430 --> 00:54:15,430
Why is it so complicated to put together a chamber orchestra?

574
00:54:16,800 --> 00:54:20,420
But I'm so glad you're here, Song Ah.

575
00:54:22,080 --> 00:54:23,760
Joon Young.

576
00:54:23,760 --> 00:54:25,240
Hello.

577
00:54:25,240 --> 00:54:28,650
It's been a while. I heard you returned to university?

578
00:54:28,650 --> 00:54:30,290
Yes.

579
00:54:37,680 --> 00:54:42,190
Are you two keeping your distance from each other because I'm here?

580
00:54:42,190 --> 00:54:43,750
Sorry?

581
00:54:45,100 --> 00:54:47,870
I heard you two are dating.

582
00:54:49,300 --> 00:54:50,960
- No, we aren't. 
 - We aren't.

583
00:54:50,960 --> 00:54:53,280
You're not?

584
00:54:53,280 --> 00:54:56,360
The rumor reached the professors' council.

585
00:54:56,360 --> 00:54:59,380
Song Ah, none of the professors knew who you were, but—

586
00:54:59,380 --> 00:55:01,790
We're not.

587
00:55:01,790 --> 00:55:04,030
We really aren't.

588
00:55:08,000 --> 00:55:11,260
If you're not, then you aren't. Why are you being so serious?

589
00:55:11,260 --> 00:55:13,700
You're making me embarrassed.

590
00:55:13,700 --> 00:55:15,750
My apologies.

591
00:55:16,450 --> 00:55:19,450
But that rumor really isn't true.

592
00:55:21,330 --> 00:55:24,000
Alright. I got it.

593
00:55:25,310 --> 00:55:27,590
Wait a second.

594
00:55:27,590 --> 00:55:30,400
Yes, Hae Na?

595
00:55:30,400 --> 00:55:32,070
What?

596
00:55:34,130 --> 00:55:38,060
Really? Well, it can't be helped then. Okay, I got it.

597
00:55:38,060 --> 00:55:39,420
Yes...

598
00:55:39,420 --> 00:55:41,640
Oh my, this girl really.

599
00:55:42,740 --> 00:55:46,990
Song Ah! Do you want to take a master class?

600
00:55:46,990 --> 00:55:48,230
I'm sorry?

601
00:55:48,230 --> 00:55:52,510
I had asked Hae Na, but she says she's sick.

602
00:55:52,510 --> 00:55:56,460
It'll start soon. If you don't have any class, do you want to do it?

603
00:55:58,480 --> 00:56:01,720
You can get a private lesson for your entrance exam piece.

604
00:56:02,890 --> 00:56:07,430
It's for the recruitment of a new professor. Her name is Lee Jung Kyung.

605
00:56:09,120 --> 00:56:11,430
You don't have to do it.

606
00:56:16,380 --> 00:56:18,350
I'll do it.

607
00:56:20,090 --> 00:56:22,830
I want to get that lesson.

608
00:56:22,830 --> 00:56:28,120
Well, for the master class, you'll be fine as long as you don't do a big mistake.

609
00:56:28,120 --> 00:56:31,390
The recital is important.

610
00:56:31,390 --> 00:56:34,130
You have to get many points from that recital.

611
00:56:34,130 --> 00:56:38,060
So you really have to find a good pianist as your accompanist.

612
00:56:38,060 --> 00:56:39,640
Got it?

613
00:56:39,640 --> 00:56:41,390
Yes.

614
00:56:43,230 --> 00:56:47,590
Won't you be uncomfortable with Jung Kyung?

615
00:56:50,530 --> 00:56:53,260
I won't be comfortable, for sure.

616
00:56:55,010 --> 00:57:01,870
But you know... My feelings for you are important,

617
00:57:01,870 --> 00:57:08,600
but there are other things I like and want to do well, too.

618
00:57:10,610 --> 00:57:16,740
For now, the entrance examination for graduate school is really important to me.

619
00:57:17,650 --> 00:57:23,210
That's why I dont want to lose the opportunity to learn one more thing,

620
00:57:23,210 --> 00:57:27,370
just because I was swayed by my emotions.

621
00:57:37,120 --> 00:57:39,230
I'll get going.

622
00:57:51,850 --> 00:57:55,470
About the rumor, the professor talked about earlier.

623
00:57:58,050 --> 00:58:02,620
I am disconcerted such a rumor is going around, but...

624
00:58:09,260 --> 00:58:11,530
I'm saddened.

625
00:58:14,760 --> 00:58:18,770
You were denying it so much in front of me...

626
00:58:20,620 --> 00:58:23,550
that it saddened me, strangely.

627
00:58:26,690 --> 00:58:29,550
I did it because of you.

628
00:58:31,040 --> 00:58:34,750
Because I was afraid you'd be put in a tough spot because of that rumor.

629
00:58:36,040 --> 00:58:38,320
I was worried.

630
00:58:46,420 --> 00:58:49,260
Please don't talk like that.

631
00:58:50,630 --> 00:58:54,150
Those words might not be anything special for you,

632
00:58:54,910 --> 00:59:02,760
but each sentence of yours, and every little action, it all stays on my mind.

633
00:59:06,490 --> 00:59:12,370
But now... I don't want to be like that anymore.

634
00:59:13,050 --> 00:59:14,660
Song Ah.

635
00:59:14,660 --> 00:59:16,560
Joon Young.

636
00:59:23,400 --> 00:59:27,340
Good thing you're here. I had something to tell you.

637
00:59:29,260 --> 00:59:32,860
Please be my accompanist for my recital.

638
00:59:34,030 --> 00:59:40,990


639
00:59:43,110 --> 00:59:44,950
No.

640
00:59:53,030 --> 00:59:57,360
I won't be your accompanist.

641
00:59:58,250 --> 01:00:06,000
♫   I'm reminded again of you who drifted away   ♫

642
01:00:06,000 --> 01:00:10,420
♫   Though I loved you   ♫

643
01:00:12,730 --> 01:00:18,100
♫   The radiant memories of our past days  ♫

644
01:00:18,100 --> 01:00:25,410
    
 ♫   come visit me again.   ♫

645
01:00:26,520 --> 01:00:33,340
♫   In the end, I wasn't able to forget anything about you   ♫

646
01:00:33,340 --> 01:00:38,850
♫   I must have loved you too much   ♫

647
01:00:38,850 --> 01:00:43,290
♫   Because I miss you   ♫

648
01:00:43,290 --> 01:00:46,990
♫  I cry out your name   ♫

649
01:00:46,990 --> 01:00:50,000
♫   Even if it's just a lingering attachment  ♫

650
01:00:50,000 --> 01:00:54,110
♫  I'll have no regrets   ♫

651
01:00:54,110 --> 01:01:02,770
♫   Can you hear my heartfelt story?  ♫

652
01:01:02,770 --> 01:01:09,390
♫   Without you, I'm nothing   ♫

653
01:01:10,610 --> 01:01:12,420
 Dong Yoon cancelled his blind date? 

654
01:01:12,420 --> 01:01:14,770
 Could it be because of me? Because he's concerned about me? 

655
01:01:14,770 --> 01:01:15,950
 Song Ah, I... 

656
01:01:15,950 --> 01:01:16,900
 Why would you come here? 

657
01:01:16,900 --> 01:01:18,060
 It's all my fault.  

658
01:01:18,060 --> 01:01:18,950
 What is your fault? 

659
01:01:18,950 --> 01:01:20,690
 Unni, are you dating Park Joon Young? 

660
01:01:20,690 --> 01:01:23,270
 Do you think a world-class person would date an average music school student? 

661
01:01:23,270 --> 01:01:25,550
 Is that why you've been constantly pushing me away these days? 

662
01:01:25,550 --> 01:01:29,290
 Each sentence of yours, and every little action, stays on my mind, Song Ah. 

663
01:01:29,290 --> 01:01:31,600
 Song Ah, I... 

664
01:01:31,600 --> 01:01:37,220
♫   Were yours the same as you turned away?   ♫

665
01:01:37,220 --> 01:01:40,600
♫   Because I miss you  ♫

